org.strongback.command

Enum CommandState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CommandState>
      • org.strongback.command.CommandState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<CommandState>

    public enum CommandState
extends Enum<CommandState>
    Defines the current state of a Command. The state transition is as follows: 
       UNINITIALIZED ----> RUNNING ----> FINISHED ----> FINALIZED
        |                 |             |
        |                 |             |
        +-----------------+-------------+----> INTERRUPTED
    However, a command in any state state may transition to INTERRUPTED.
    1. UNINITIALIZED - The Command has not been initialized or executed yet.
    2. RUNNING - The Command has been initialized and executed at least once.
    3. INTERUPTED - The Command has been interrupted, but it has not been processed.
    4. FINISHED - The Command has finished but has not been finalized.
    5. FINALIZED - The Command has finished and been cleaned up.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      FINALIZED
      The Command has completed running and is ready to be finished.
      FINISHED
      The Command has completed running (because Command.execute() returned true).
      INTERUPTED
      The Command has been interrupted before completion, but the interrupt has not been processed.
      RUNNING
      The Command has been initialized and is ready to executed.
      UNINITIALIZED
      The Command is ready to be initialized.
